700108f-a.text:
352 to 364 East 145th Street, south side, Just east of Third Avenue, and the "El.: The two buildings in view 1 are Nos. 352 and 356; the factory, in view 2 is No. 358-364. It was formerly a warehouse, erected in 1882, and is now the store fixtures manufacturing plant of Silverberg and Trattner.
P. L. Sperr  April 29, 1941
No Reproductions  Views 1, 2
